text: Not to spoil the film for any of you who want to see it but I have already checked the reviews and most critics have panned this third outing... not to mention Rotten Tomatoes has only given it a twenty-seven percent approval rating. Now, if you are the kind of viewer whose opinion of a film is not swayed by what critics think that's fine but I have always taken the opinions of critics into account. Something just tells me they're right. I enjoyed the first film but to me signs of this franchise sinking appeared in the sequel which was weaker in my opinion. What I found so frustrating in the sequel is how Anna Kendrick's character Becky went from the rebel who didn't take crap from anybody to a wimpy pushover. Once again, anybody who wants to see this film shouldn't let my comment deter them from doing so but I have no plans to see it.

text: As a music and singing fan, listening to the renditions they performed while doing the USO Shows brought back memories. When the last songs were shown,(all 3 movies)¬†each time the emotion that was brought out... of me.... was unbelievable. You cant help but be happy for what they achieved, and the singing was spot on.When¬†PP 3 ending song came on, Freedom 90 Anna's voice is so smooth, soft and powerful all at the same time... Just like DJ Kahlid said.... Goosebumps. I watched the end song on¬† a free movie weekend 10 times, and I get the same feeling every time.I guess I got the Music in Me.BTW... The one liners were so fast and funny, better then the idiots on late night, and John Lithgow was great also... Don't forget the jokes by John & Gail throughout the movie.Mike White, great thoughtful writer, Don't forget the School of Rock.Favorite Girls, Anna Camp, Britany Snow, Anna Kendrick.... In ANY ORDER!
